Igdoside A ( 2 ) appeared as a yellow amorphous powder. Its molecular formula, C 37 H 46 O 18 , was determined based on the negative HRESIMS ion ( Figure S3 ) observed at m/z 777.2233 [M – H] (calcd. 778.2684). The UV spectrum (DMSO) of 2 displayed two absorption maxima (log ε ) at 283 (4.25) and 362 (4.18) nm, indicating its flavonol skeleton. The 1 H and 13 C-NMR spectra ( Table 2 , Figures S4 and S 5 ) showed the typical pattern of a flavonol acyl glycoside. Owing to the presence of two meta-coupled protons for ring A (δ 6.49 and 6.76, d, J = 2.0 Hz), an ABX system signal for ring B (δ 6.91 d, J = 8.4 Hz, 7.61 dd, J = 8.3, 2.2 Hz, and 8.04 d, J = 2.2 Hz), and one singlet signal at δ 3.97 for a methoxy group, the compound 2 aglycon was identified as isorhamnetin (
;
). Two anomeric protons from the sugar moieties appeared at δ 5.40 ( J = 7.7 Hz) and 5.61 ( J = 1.4 Hz); these protons were found to respectively correlate with signals at δ 102.7 and 98.3 in the HMQC spectrum. COSY and HMQC ( Figures S6 and S 7) experiments led to the identification of one β -galactopyranosyl and one α -rhamnopyranosyl sugar unit. Furthermore, the 1 H-NMR spectrum ( Table 2 , Figure S4 ) revealed the presence of a quaternary methyl (δ 1.30, s), an olefinic methyl (δ 1.90, d, J = 3.4 Hz), a terminal olefin (δ 5.08, dd, J = 10.8, 1.5 Hz, δ 5.25, dd, J = 17.4, 1.5 Hz, δ 5.95, ddd, J = 17.4, 10.8, 1.5 Hz), an olefinic proton (δ 6.96, m), and two methylene protons (δ 1.67 and 2.30, m). These protons correlated with signals at δ 11.1 and 26.4 for methyl carbons; δ 23.2, 40.3, and 111.0 for methylene carbons; and δ 143.2 and 144.5 for methyn carbons. In addition, two quaternary carbons (δ 127.2 and 72.2) and one ester carbon (δ 168.1) are seen in the 13 C-NMR spectrum ( Table 2 , Figure S5 ), and δ 6.96 (m) and 1.90 (d, J = 3.4) were found to correlate with δ 168.1. These findings suggest that this compound is an ester of the monoterpenoid, α,β -unsaturated carboxylic acid. The correlations between H-1 (δ 5.40) of galactose and C-3 of aglycone (δ 134.2), H-1 of rhamnose (δ 5.61) and C-7 of aglycone (δ 161.9), and H-4 of rhamnose (δ 5.18) and C-1 of acyl (δ 168.0) were detected in the HMBC spectrum ( Fig. 2 and S 8) of 2 . As a result of these interactions, β -D-Gal-(1 → 3)-Agl, α -L-Rham-(1 → 7)-Agl, and Acyl-(1 → 4)- α -L-Rham linkages were detected. Compound 2 was thus identified as isorhamnetin-3- O -β -D-galactopyranosyl-7- O -[2,6-dimethyl-6-hydroxy-2, 7-octadienoyl-(1 → 4)]- α -L-rhamnopyranoside (igdoside A).

